Create a platform that helps users discover, compare, and track video game prices across multiple online stores and platforms in real time.

The experience should feel extremely simple, fast, and conversational.

The user starts by entering the name of a game. The system searches for matching games and identifies the correct game entry. Once selected, the platform gathers pricing and deal information from multiple stores and platforms.

The platform should then:

Compare all available prices
Detect the best current deal
Show discount percentages
Show historical lows if available
Recommend the best platform/store to buy from
Provide direct purchase links

The recommendation system should not only choose the cheapest option, but also consider factors like:

Store reliability
Historical pricing trends
Discount quality
Regional pricing
Availability
User preference for a specific platform/store

After seeing the results, the user should have multiple options:

Buy immediately using the direct store link
Track the game price across all stores
Track the game only on a selected store/platform
Set a target price and get notified when the game reaches it

The tracking system should support:

Flexible tracking duration
Custom notification frequency
Continuous price monitoring
Independent tracking across all stores
Store-specific tracking
Smart deal monitoring

The platform should continuously monitor prices in the background and fetch fresh pricing data periodically. Whenever a better deal or target price is detected, the user should instantly receive a notification.

The product should heavily focus on automation and conversational interactions.

The ideal experience is:

Minimal manual work
Quick setup
Fast results
Natural interaction flow

The platform should also support a conversational assistant or chat-based experience where users can simply type messages like:

“Track Elden Ring”
“Notify me when GTA V drops below ₹1000”
“Best deal for Cyberpunk right now”
“Track Steam prices only”

The assistant should guide users step-by-step by:

Showing matching games
Displaying available deals
Asking follow-up questions
Setting up tracking automatically
Sending deal alerts later

The system should feel like a personal gaming deal assistant.

The platform should eventually evolve into a smart recommendation and prediction engine capable of:

Predicting upcoming sales
Identifying likely future discounts
Explaining why a deal is good
Recommending the best time to buy
Understanding user preferences and favorite platforms

The long-term vision is to create a centralized intelligent deal-tracking ecosystem for gamers that removes the need to manually compare stores or monitor prices themselves.

Core goals:

Save users money
Save users time
Simplify deal discovery
Automate price tracking
Create a seamless conversational experience
Make game price tracking effortless and addictive to use

The platform should prioritize:

Clean user experience
Fast deal retrieval
Smart recommendations
Reliable tracking
Real-time notifications
Conversational simplicity
High retention and repeat usage

The entire product should feel modern, automated, intelligent, and highly user-centric.